======================================================================
PART 5: The π/4 connection — Leibniz series
======================================================================
  The Dirichlet L-function L(1, χ_p) for χ_p = (·/p):
  L(1, χ_p) = Σ_{n=1}^∞ (n/p)/n = (π/√p) × h(-p)/w(-p)
  where h(-p) is the class number of Q(√-p)

  p=3: L(1, χ_p) ≈ 0.60459645
    π/√p = 1.81379936
    L × √p / π = 0.33333150 (should be h/1 for large p)
  p=7: L(1, χ_p) ≈ 1.18742041
    π/√p = 1.18741041
    L × √p / π = 1.00000842 (should be h/1 for large p)
  p=11: L(1, χ_p) ≈ 0.94722583
    π/√p = 0.94722583
    L × √p / π = 1.00000000 (should be h/1 for large p)
  p=19: L(1, χ_p) ≈ 0.72072078
    π/√p = 0.72073078
    L × √p / π = 0.99998612 (should be h/1 for large p)
  p=23: L(1, χ_p) ≈ 1.96521205
    π/√p = 0.65506735
    L × √p / π = 3.00001527 (should be h/1 for large p)

